                                                        2. Heat a non-stick skillet over medium heat and lightly coat it with cooking spray or olive oil.<br />
                                                        3. Add the diced bell peppers and onions to the skillet and sauté for 2-3 minutes until they begin to soften.<br />
                                                        4. Add the diced tomatoes and chopped spinach to the skillet and cook for an additional 1-2 minutes until the spinach wilts.<br />
                                                        5. Remove the vegetable mixture from the skillet and set it aside.<br />
                                                        6. Re-grease the skillet with cooking spray or a small amount of olive oil if needed.<br />
                                                        7. Pour the beaten egg whites into the skillet and let them spread evenly.<br />
                                                        8. Cook the egg whites for 1-2 minutes until the edges start to set.<br />
                                                        9. Spoon the vegetable mixture evenly onto one half of the omelet.<br />
                                                        10. Gently fold the other half of the omelet over the vegetables to form a semi-circle.<br />
                                                        11. Cook the omelet for another 1-2 minutes until the egg whites are fully cooked.<br />
                                                        12. Carefully transfer the omelet to a plate and serve hot.<br />
